PHASE A — FIX FAILING FLOWS
============================

Step A1: Run the full suite and collect results.

  cd /Users/karthik_sivam/Documents/My\ Apps/SmartInventory/smart-inventory
  maestro test maestro/flows/01_onboarding.yaml 2>&1 | tail -5
  maestro test maestro/run_all_simulator.sh 2>&1 > maestro_phase_a_results.log

  (If run_all_simulator.sh doesn't exist, run individual flows sequentially
  from 01 to 80.)

Step A2: For each failing flow, diagnose the root cause:
  a) "Element not found" — the element text or id has changed in the UI.
     Open the view file for that screen in AITest/Views/ and find the current
     .accessibilityIdentifier or visible text. Update the YAML to match.
  b) "Timeout waiting for app" — add a longer timeout or an intermediate wait.
  c) "App not in foreground" — add a launchApp step at the top of the flow.
  d) Flows that depend on state from prior flows — make the flow self-contained
     by including the appropriate helper at the top.

Step A3: Common fixes to apply across all flows:
  - If a flow taps a nav tab by icon and fails, switch to tapOn with the
    accessibility label text ("Dashboard", "Items", "Profile").
  - If assertVisible fails on a translated/dynamic string, switch to
    assertVisible with id: instead of text:.
  - After fixing, re-run the individual flow to confirm it passes.

Step A4: Update maestro/README.md with any flows that were fixed, noting
  what changed and why.

